  "text": "The CRD validation schema to OpenAPI schema publishing chain in Kubernetes involves the following transformation pipeline:\n\n**1. CRD Validation Schema Definition**\nThe CustomResourceDefinition API object stores its validation schema in the `spec.Validation.OpenAPIV3Schema` field, which is of type `JSONSchemaProps`. This is defined in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apis/apiextensions/types.go` (internal API) and `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apis/apiextensions/v1/types.go` (v1 API).\n\n**2. JSONSchemaProps to go-openapi Conversion (Validation Module)**\nThe `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/validation/validation.go` file implements the conversion from JSONSchemaProps to go-openapi spec.Schema:\n- `ConvertJSONSchemaProps()` - Direct conversion wrapper\n- `ConvertJSONSchemaPropsWithPostProcess()` - Main conversion function with optional post-processing\n- `NewSchemaValidator()` - Creates validators from JSONSchemaProps by converting to OpenAPI schema\n\n**3. Structural Schema Extraction**\nThe `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/schema/convert.go` implements `NewStructural()` which converts JSONSchemaProps to a structural schema representation (defined in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/schema/structural.go`). Structural schemas enforce Kubernetes' stricter validation invariants and are required for many features including field management and pruning.\n\n**4. Structural Schema to OpenAPI v3 Conversion**\nThe `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/schema/kubeopenapi.go` file implements the `ToKubeOpenAPI()` method on the Structural type, which converts the internal structural representation back to the standard go-openapi spec.Schema format for publication.\n\n**5. OpenAPI Builder (Web Service Construction)**\nThe `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/controller/openapi/builder/builder.go` file contains:\n- `BuildOpenAPIV2()` - Builds complete OpenAPI v2 specification for a CRD version\n- `BuildOpenAPIV3()` - Builds complete OpenAPI v3 specification for a CRD version\nThese functions construct RestfulAPI web service routes and use kube-openapi builders to generate the complete spec from the structural schema.\n\n**6. OpenAPI Controller (Dynamic Spec Management)**\nThe `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/controller/openapi/controller.go` implements the OpenAPI controller which:\n- Watches CustomResourceDefinition changes via informers\n- Builds merged OpenAPI v2 specs for all served CRD versions\n- Lazily constructs and caches specs per CRD\n- Updates the OpenAPIService to publish updated specs\n\nThe OpenAPI v3 controller is implemented in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/controller/openapiv3/controller.go` with similar functionality.\n\n**7. OpenAPI v2 Conversion Support**\nThe `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/controller/openapi/v2/conversion.go` provides `ToStructuralOpenAPIV2()` to convert structural schemas to OpenAPI v2-compatible format when v2 specs are needed.\n\n**8. API Server Endpoint Registration and Publication**\nThe `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/routes/openapi.go` file implements:\n- `InstallV2()` - Registers the /openapi/v2 HTTP endpoint\n- `InstallV3()` - Registers the /openapi/v3 HTTP endpoint\nThese endpoints serve the aggregated OpenAPI specifications built by the controllers.\n\nThe `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/apiserver.go` file orchestrates the startup:\n- Creates the OpenAPI controller(s) after the API server is ready\n- Passes the static OpenAPI spec and OpenAPIService to the controller\n- The controller merges CRD specs with the static spec and publishes via the registered endpoints\n\n**Complete Flow:**\nCustomResourceDefinition (OpenAPIV3Schema: JSONSchemaProps) → ConvertJSONSchemaProps (JSONSchemaProps → spec.Schema) → NewStructural (JSONSchemaProps → Structural) → ToKubeOpenAPI (Structural → spec.Schema) → BuildOpenAPIV2/V3 (WebService + spec.Schema → full OpenAPI spec) → OpenAPI Controller (merges and caches per CRD) → HTTP endpoints (/openapi/v2, /openapi/v3)\n"
}

